ğŸ§  How It Works
Core Types

DietaryTag â€” union of supported diet tags (vegan, vegetarian, gluten-free, etc.)

Cuisine â€” a set of cuisines (Italian, Indian, Thai, etc.)

Recipe â€” normalized structure for generated recipes:

title, description, cuisine, servings, timeMinutes

dietary: DietaryTag[]

ingredients: string[]

steps: string[]

tips?: string[]

caloriesPerServing?: number

Generation Pipeline

Normalize pantry: split by comma/newline â†’ trim â†’ de-dupe

Diet filter: remove entries incompatible with selected dietary tags

Main ingredient: pick a likely â€œcenterpieceâ€ (regex match: chicken/tofu/lentil/etc.)

Flavor accent: sample from FLAVOR_MAP based on cuisine

Style selection: e.g. bowls, curry, stir-fry, tacos

Title template: interpolate ${cuisine}, ${main}, ${accent}

Ingredients: combine sampled pantry with a small â€œbase pantryâ€ (oil, aromatics)

Steps: build a short, realistic sequence (aromatics â†’ protein/veg â†’ body/sauce â†’ balance â†’ serve)

Calories (heuristic): simple word-based scoring to estimate kcal/serving

Tips: sample a few useful cooking tips

All randomness is simple Math.random() sampling for lightweight, deterministic-ish variety.






